In the Matter of Louis HAMBURGER, Bankrupt; Commercial Investment Trust, Inc., Petitioner. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. January 25, 1924.) No. 226. Leo Oppenheimer, of New York City (Leo N. Hiblum, of New York City, of counsel), for petitioner. Tanzer & Lane, of New York City (Charles J. Lane, of New York City, of counsel), for respondent.

Before HOUGH, MANTON, and MAYER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Petition dismissed, without prejudice, in open court.
